{"text": "Found this randomly on my Steam list the other day, decided to give it a shot and read it during most of my free time and finished it within a couple of days. Enjoyed the hell out of the story, I think it is worth going through for that alone and I think I will remember it for a long time. My only complaint for this is that the UI is quite clunky (Specifically the game does not let you know that it is waiting for input: there's no moving arrow indicator at the end of the text or anything like that like which you would find in most VNs) but that is a minor complaint, it is well-worth putting up with due to the enjoyable story and characters. It is very mixed-genre, there are both a lot of well-described action sequences as well as more slice-of-life-like parts with a lot of character development. I have seen other reviewers on here mention that you can't save your game mid-chapter, this is not true. I was able to save at any point using the right-click menu. I hope that the other scenarios get translated too at some point, but this one forms a complete-enough story on its own and is well worth reading.", "appid": "392370", "steamid": "profiles/76561197995695999", "voted_up": true, "votes_up": 0, "votes_funny": 0, "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1563969600.0}
