{"text": "This is so incredibly fun! As some of you know this is from a concept that was created in college by the guys, it was called nitronic rush. After what they have achieved from there to Distance is particularly amazing!  I had in my mind that this was early access (just released as early access on december the 10th). As soon as i got into playing the visuals are spot on, the gameplay is extremely fun and addicting and the overall concept is great. Yes, then i discovered the mechanics: Boosting, jumping, flying and wall jumping; crazy stuff like that! I can't even begin to explain the potential this game has, at the moment it actually is decently polished but not many official levels and progression pointers and goals, i'd imagine that to be fun. But there is the community making levels and there is a powerful level editor, it's nice that it has that. There is the Adventure mode which is short at the moment (and there isn't a story to it really). Arcade mode which has various gamemodes in it to play your community levels and official levels.  Yes, i do. If you'd like to support it at it's current state i'd definetley reccomend for you to purchase it. It also has multiplayer and a friendly community which is great!   Trackmania, LittleBigPlanet Karting.", "appid": "233610", "steamid": "profiles/76561198071130114", "voted_up": true, "votes_up": "6", "votes_funny": "1", "early_access": true, "tstamp_created": 1419249600.0}
