{"text": "After reading the recent reviews, all which are negative, I think people are only looking at the bad side of things. Honestly, the only reason why I bought this game, and this is my personal opinion, is because it called to me. After buying and playing this game for some time I began to like it more and more, the game does not always have to be perfect for you to like it, you as a person have to look at its bright sides. Why do you think we never really talk about the other side of the moon, because it is unimportant to us, it does not matter since we have the light on the other side to show how beautiful it is. Same with Just Survive, we shouldn't look at the part of it that does not shine because by its self, even if we could use an update here and there and some fixes should be met I still think we should at least thank the developers for the game it is now for it could be far worse then it is at this very moment.", "appid": "295110", "steamid": "profiles/76561198139429706", "voted_up": true, "votes_up": "7", "votes_funny": "2", "early_access": true, "tstamp_created": 1525003200.0}
{"text": "DanganRonpa Another Episode Ultra Despair Girls isn`t like its predecessors. The game uses different mechanics and gimmicks, the gameplay itself is clearly different from DanganRonpa 1 and 2. This game is a third-person shooter with visual novel elements (and a lot of animation). The story was pretty good and fills in the gaps in the DanganRonpa series overall. Playing this game before DR1 and DR2 is not advised, the plot of the previous games is massively spoiled. You`ll have to play this after finishing DanganRonpa 2 and before the DanganRonpa 3 anime.", "appid": "555950", "steamid": "profiles/76561198161727032", "voted_up": true, "votes_up": "7", "votes_funny": 0, "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1498910400.0}
