{"text": "I'm surprised AF has as many negative reviews as it does considering it delivers on its promise of a GTA-like in a mid-american small town setting. The game plays great on a gamepad and has enough variety with mission types plus side activities that you shouldn't get bored before you finish the game's main campaign. The graphics and aesthetics are quite good for a top down game and the music though relatively sparse and a tad generic sets a proper tone for the action. The thief/robber minigame that occurs when you enter structures works very well for what it is and lets you get down to purloining with minimum fuss. The cars handle just fine and with good differentiation in how they perform and feel depending on model. Lots of guns and vehicles to wreck mayhem with as well. Just think of GTAs usual weapon variety and they pretty much got a similar selection in this game up to a minigun and rocket launcher. Only thing that's missing is being able to fly a chopper basically. So basically if you like top down games and gtalikes well I just don't see how you could dislike this game. It does get a bit buggy/glitchy at times but it only affected me in a mission or two and nothing a mission restart didn't fix. The missions aren't that long and the ones that aren't that short usually have checkpoints you can restart from so it's a minor issue. Ok, that's that. See you on the lam!", "appid": "934780", "steamid": "profiles/76561198034315837", "voted_up": true, "votes_up": "64", "votes_funny": "2", "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1600516800.0}
