{"text": "I was only interested in the campaign to which i refer in this review.  The length of the story is ok (as expected for cod conditions) and completed after 11 missions, although it was fast-paced in the end. The story is told around the main protagonist Daniels who fights with his squad through well designed battlefields.  The cutscenes were animated excellently and the atmosphere is very good. I would also rate the game mechanics as good. That's why i can definitely recommend the game to people who just want to play the campaign like me. But i would wait for a good offer, because the original price for the few hours is a bit high.", "appid": "476600", "steamid": "profiles/76561198056344396", "voted_up": true, "votes_up": "1", "votes_funny": 0, "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1598443200.0}
{"text": "The game is pure masterpiece 10/10 if you ready to deal with checkpoint saves and scripted linear gameplay in 2020. UPD after playing more hours:  Okay, now I slightly hate this game for not having saving system. Checkpoint system in 2020! FFS, developers. This is a PC not a console game. The game becomes monotonous and too slow sometimes when in scripted scene you just HAVE TO wait until some character says its speech or move to another area. The stealth gameplay is awful and I don't really understand why developers included it in the game. I dropped the game with rage quit when for the n-th time I had to replay some sequence. The cut-scenes are too long and sometimes boring. Yes, the story is still great for now but the further you advance the more cut-scenes you see. I started to skip some of them. Puzzles somewhat stupid and not obvious every time. Maybe I just stupid. I give this game one more chance until I drop it and change the review to \"not recommended\".", "appid": "752590", "steamid": "profiles/76561198026971270", "voted_up": true, "votes_up": 0, "votes_funny": 0, "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1595160000.0}
