{"text": "A bit of point & click history, \"Noctrop\" (it was a DOS game afterall) works nicely on Steam. Sure, it's a little bit clunky by today's standards but it (still) gives me a Candyman vibe when playing which I appreciate. Never beat it when I was younger but just replayed and it wasn't too difficult and I enjoyed seeing the story through to the end, achievements are a nice addition which helped motivate me to progress. A raw 90's point & click, even if a little simplistic compared to its kin but if you like that sort of thing you'll certainly like something about this. Note: It's for adults, 90's adults to be fair - simpler times, but boobs are boobs no matter what year it is. Store page doesn't appear to warn of that.", "appid": "377070", "steamid": "profiles/76561198070948222", "voted_up": true, "votes_up": "2", "votes_funny": 0, "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1569067200.0}
