{"text": "Just to start with, I have never played chivalry. The tutorial gives you alot of info on the game, if you dont do it, then your first matches will be hell. The mechanics of the game are awesome, there are lots and lots of playstyles and techniques. Frontline is very hectic and very fun, it gives nearly no coins and exp tho, they should buff it. Battle royale is an overall fun experience, but it has not much players. Horde is awesome, there's alot of teamwork involved. One thing I don't like tho is the prices of certain armor. People just keep running infront of the bots and keep hitting 1 by 1, the maps should have more flank points on horde imo. There's also an option to browse through community run servers, such as duel servers. Duel servers are awesome to learn advanced moves and to improve your overall skill. 80% of the players there follow the rules and are very kind towards each other. I never played any other community run server so I don't have info on that. Gameplay 9/10 Mechanics 10/10 Fun 8/10", "appid": "629760", "steamid": "profiles/76561198401163139", "voted_up": true, "votes_up": 0, "votes_funny": 0, "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1559304000.0}
