{"text": "Subnautica is incredible. The atmosphere the game creates is one of the most immersive I've ever found in a game. The rest of the gameplay is simple and clean, the story is pretty interesting/well delivered, but it's that atmosphere that really makes the game. You really feel the tension as you're drifting down into the abyss where the light ends and visibility drops to almost nothing. The different environments are unique and well designed, the creatures are creative and interesting, the crafting system is intuitive, and the story makes you want to find all the pieces to figure out what's going on.  As for the horror aspect, I imagine every single person who plays it has the same expression on their face the first time they see/get caught by a reaper, and all the creature sounds can be unsettling. I definitely recommend headphones with it; preferably something sound cancelling to remove distractions and let you really zone in. The soundscape is very well done and adds so much to the experience. The darkness of the ocean, leviathans and other freaky creatures, the feeling of being vulnerable under water. The entire game just absorbed me and I was totally immersed in it. It's the balance of hope and progression with helplessness and panic that makes Subnautica a truly great horror game.", "appid": "264710", "steamid": "profiles/76561198064495367", "voted_up": true, "votes_up": "121", "votes_funny": "6", "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1572004800.0}
