{"text": "I have a mixed feeling about this game. On paper the concept seems creative and original. The gameplay is very easy to understand and the music and sound effects are fun to listen. But it becomes repetetive really fast. After the first 8-10 levels, all you do is basically click around the center of the field, then hope for the best. In most cases the level is cleared, if not: Repeat until it is cleared. Altogether, you can beat all levels in around 20-30 minutes. So, this game is playable, can be fun for a short amount of time and it's price it pretty fair, but if you are looking for something puzzle-ish with strategy, this game is not for you.", "appid": "987570", "steamid": "profiles/76561198019862191", "voted_up": true, "votes_up": "1", "votes_funny": 0, "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1565006400.0}
