{"text": "Oh, Stardew Valley. The game that has reached it's way to every console possible. It deserves every sale it makes. I received this game when I purchased Humble Bundle Monthly, back in November of 2016. Back then, I wasn't too interested in it. I admit, I didn't really look into it and I was motivated to try it. I did eventually get to trying it, and I stopped playing after 15 minutes. Oh boy, do I regret that. This game has to be one of the best indies to ever be released. Not only does this game have tons of fun things to do, but even the simple base game is relaxing and enjoyable. I'm so glad that my friend forced me to play it with her, as I fell in love with this game. I now own it on Steam and Nintendo Switch, and I don't regret any of the hours I have spent playing this game. It's all been enjoyable and worth while. This game does a great job as to giving you multiple things to do and level up. It's also a plus that leveling up actually changes the game. There are also collectibles that are quite enjoyable to hunt and retrieve. Never have I been disappointed in this game. The detail that has been put into this game is remarkable as well. ConcernedApe, I hope other developers look up to you and that this product inspires them.  Thank you for making this game, and sticking with it.", "appid": "413150", "steamid": "profiles/76561198091191236", "voted_up": true, "votes_up": "1", "votes_funny": 0, "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1542974400.0}
