{"text": "Hide and Shriek is a multiplayer horror game where your goal is to find orbs and scare your friends. Since there's no story, we're jumping straight into graphics. Graphics: Hide and Shriek only has one map which is a school, which consists of a few different rooms and a hallway filled with lockers. Since the main goal of the game is to look for hidden orbs, there's a ton of detail in every room of the game. You go in a classroom and shelfs will be filled with books, beakers and all other items you can find in a school.  Another thing is the screamer masks and they can be customized with different items, however you need to unlock most cosmetic items, so I couldn't check them all out, but what I saw looked really cool. However there's a limited amount of these for the free version of the game and you get more for buying the mask pack, but I wouldn't do that. Audio: The audio design in my opinion is a very mixed bag. Once the game gets going there's a bunch of stuff going on at the same time which gets really confusing once the game gets really going. There's a lot of clanging noises, lighting going outside. Audio mush is the best way I can describe it and I honestly don't really like it. Gameplay: Hide and Shriek is a 1V1 game where you compete for most points. Each round lasts around 10 minutes and the goal is to either A) Have the most points by the time clock hits 0 or B) Scare the other player three times in a row. You collect points by picking up an orb with the assigned color to you and bringing it to your altar, you also get points by collecting runes and every time you mess with the other player. In the map there's runes that have different spells assigned to them (which are also picked randomly at the start of the game). You can pick up multiple ones and combine them for more powerful spells to mess with the player. Also you have a shriek meter, which builds over time and once it's full you can jumpscare the other player and once you do that three times in a row, you win, but be careful, if you get jumpscared your streak gets reset.  You can't see the other player so you mostly orient yourself with your surroundings, for example him carrying an orb or interacting with doors. If you want to get a sneaky shriek you will have to be really mindful of your surroundings and be careful, cause your opponent will likely do the same.  Hide and Shriek is a ton of fun, but sadly there's a few issues that plague the game. One thing is the connection, it's possible to be so laggy that you will not be able to do anything. Your orbs will be stuck, you can't shriek the other player and other stuff which make the game difficult to play. One other thing is if you get a bad set of runes, the other player will literally cheese the game by collecting tracking runes and just jumpscaring you, which gets incredibly boring.  Another thing is the game is pretty much dead. Depending on the day and the time, it will be unlikely you will find a match. I once had a day where I could get into a match instantly and then I get a day where I simply can't find a match. Now for that reason alone I would give a game negative score, but since the game is a 1V1 you only need another friend to tag along and play which is easier than let's say 7 friends for one match to get started. Verdict: Hide and Shriek is fun concept, but sadly it gets incredibly boring pretty fast. Since it's free it might be fun to get a friend and have a few matches and have a few laughs along the way and overall it's fun enough to try to burn a couple hours away, just don't be disappointed if you can't get into a match. Final Rating: 6/10 Pros: + Fun gameplay + Unique concept Cons: - Most lobbies end up being really laggy - Pretty much dead  If you liked this review please consider joining   and", "appid": "480430", "steamid": "profiles/76561198043609914", "voted_up": true, "votes_up": "9", "votes_funny": 0, "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1603800000.0}
{"text": "Hands down, for me, this is one of the best things I have experienced in my life. It's not just a mod like many people call it, and not even a separate game, it's a personal experience, an emotional rollercoaster unlike any other thing I've experienced in almost 2 decades I've been constantly gaming. It can really touch you, make you ask yourself questions about life, morals, etc. I can't even begin to explain without giving spoilers or too much details how the endings felt after I got so invested in the game, it's story and characters. It can devastate you, and I don't think there's any other game, no matter how nostalgic I might be about it, that made me feel atleast in a similar way. Now... enough of the dramatic stuff, because like I said, I think the game is very personal, so it might make you feel completely different.  On to the game itself.  This game is a real gem. The amount of content and the way it's implemented is mind blowing. Being a fan of the old hardcore rpg Gothic series, the difficulty, leveled zones, and certain similar gameplay mechanics are really great. Wandering randomly without proper gear can really punish you for not preparing yourself. However, there are plenty rewards for those who dare to explore, and there are a LOT of places to discover in this game, and secrets to be uncovered. In the begining the story might seem overwhelming, you learn about so many things that don't seem connected, you meet interesting characters, you try to see what is causing a certain \"fever\" you are experiencing, all while have weird visions and dream sequences. As you advance the story, everything falls into place and starts to make sense. You learn the connections between everything. The plot twists in the second half of the game are the most memorable, and really tense things up as you feel an impending doom aproaching. From there on you are trying to achieve the impossible. Can you save the world? The characters are excellently written. Each one with it's personality, principles and ideas, that you will learn while interacting with them. There's also a number of side quests and special dialogue with two important characters which will dive deep into the more psychological side of the game, with certain questions about morals, what's good and what's wrong, etc. Other interactions with them include learning more about the lore, or things about themselves. The music, visuals and scenery, and overall atmosphere are all absolutely wonderful. Sure, the engine has it's hiccups, but that won't stop you from immersing yourself into this beautifully crafted world with deep lore and captivating story. In the end, I want to thank all the people who have worked hard creating this masterpiece, and hope as much people as possible get to experience it.", "appid": "933480", "steamid": "profiles/76561198149946667", "voted_up": true, "votes_up": "138", "votes_funny": "9", "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1550232000.0}
