{"text": "First off, understand it's a short film, so for all we know, it's either a demonstration, or just simply that... a short film. Even though it was only 10 minutes long, it was enough to capture my attention to details. The details of this film were the most important of all. Because the game is very simple in it's gameplay, to be able to capture the essence of what real border control goes through is very emotional. I can actually this being a full movie if they can get the details right. The idea of one man having emotional conflicts between who's worthy and who's not versus who is a good person and who is out to terrorize the nation really captured me, especially the ending of this film. I would really love to see this as a full movie. Very nice job with camera, lighting, colors, and the look/feel of early 1980's.", "appid": "804320", "steamid": "profiles/76561198022104383", "voted_up": true, "votes_up": 0, "votes_funny": 0, "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1579953600.0}
