{"text": "I am really impressed by the job done by the Crowbar Collective. I hardly remembered how good Half-Life was when I played it the first time. It was only a souvenir of a good game. After replaying the whole game, I can say that it does not get old. It still has everything you could expect from a modern FPS and that is why it was such a break through at the time. You don't have to simply shoot all your enemies, you have to think a lot. You are a scientist in the end and not a soldier. And the developers really managed to give the original a great tribute. The work on the Xen world is great and was worth the wait, the musics are engaging and the whole game is very enjoyable.", "appid": "362890", "steamid": "profiles/76561198046696031", "voted_up": true, "votes_up": "20", "votes_funny": "1", "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1587902400.0}
