{"text": "Ashes of the Singularity overall is a very good RTS which has made great progress from alpha stages to now (it's official release). I find the game excellent and have had fun playing it being an avid RTS fan, and have to say, I haven't been left dissapointed.  Gameplay: The gameplay is good, Units and factions are nicely balanced with exceptionally nice visuals. Overall, myself and a group of friends have had hours of fun playing against each other and against the AI. There's room for improvement but that can be said for any game but the devs have outlined that further improvements are coming and the game with further be refined and tweaked which is great news to hear.  The soundtrack for this game and the sound/SFX is exceptional, one of the best sound expereiences in any game and certainly the best I've heard in an RTS. the sound and music really draws you into the game, loving it.  Now, this may not be vital to some but for me it was a breath of fresh air that the developers are great on comminicating with their customers, the community. Throughout the development they were in constant communication with the community asking for feedback, getting feedback and implementing the feedback into the game. Absolutely top notch support from these guys and they provided tons of info, roadmaps and update info. Don't take my word for it check out the steam forums.  Overall I'm happy with the game and have not been left dissapointed. Like I said there is room for improvement and with the developers actively talking to the community getting feedback and basically asking what we want I think this is a great recipe for further improements down the road. I'm a happy customer and happier with the game.", "appid": "228880", "steamid": "profiles/76561198039791939", "voted_up": true, "votes_up": "7", "votes_funny": "1", "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1459512000.0}
