{"text": "Only 8 hours in, so far the story is good, and holy hell the gun play...  If nothing else this game has the weapons and fire fights perfect. It feels amazing and the weapon sound is better than any game ive played to date. If you like borderlands you will love this, and if nothing else play this game for the fights. Even if the story ends up sucking, the fights and game play are so good it wouldnt even matter. Update: 66 hours in, and holy crap this is the best game ive played in few years. So far the story is good, the gun play is amazing, physics are great. Im having a ton of fun. Even if it has a â™¥â™¥â™¥â™¥â™¥â™¥ ending i will play it again. The Jokes and memes are perhaps old/stupid, but i find myself laughing anyway. They make them fit well and thats what matters. Dead jokes can still be really funny in the right context. Give it a shot, you wont be disappointed. Update: 85 hours in, completed the main story line, still have some side quests to do. I havent even gotten to the dlc content yet. I dont know what people are talking about, this game is amazing, and the story is super good with lots of surprising moments. There is a section that says \"to be continued\" and i dont want to spoil it, but Maybe thats what people are thinking is the end, but its not the end till you get credits. Im very happy with this game, im gonna keep playing. I highly recommend. Best money i have spent on a game since the the orange box half-life collection before steam was a thing. Update: 126 hours in, im on the last dlc and im having so much fun with this game. My only complaint so far is in the guns, love, and tentacles dlc. Im fine with having a variety of characters, some with different sexual orientation, most times it develops part of the story different. However, a hole entire dlc to marry 2 men, just seems over the top. Dont get me wrong, the story was alright, but i was surprised during the main game when they admitted to being in love, should have just left it at that.", "appid": "397540", "steamid": "profiles/76561197972307804", "voted_up": true, "votes_up": 0, "votes_funny": 0, "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1593604800.0}
