{"text": "First of all, despite my very positive and cheeky review of original XCOM 2 release, i got dead tired from repititon towards my second walkthrough and basically dropped it. I had hopes this dlc will revitalize the experience with all the new guff it has, and it did, but for this price it feels like just a bunch of official MODS and not true expansion. While new changes are solid, they basically are mixed bags, and not straightforward improvements: -Chosen are very cool enemies and drop great loot, they are occasionally very challenging especially on start, but borked by terrible AI decisions and Chosen Fortress missions are basically the same unimaginative \"shot Chosen and then shot at giant stone phallic object\" 3 times in a row. Plus they complete the metamorphosis of xcom into anime with bishonen commander and  le cool villains with katanas (assassin r34 when). -Some abilities used right can wipe out Chosen, Alien ruler, sectopod and basically everything in general direction of your target (banish with superior mag and repeater turns reapers into... literally reapers?). -Covert ops are great way to level soldiers you wouldn't otherwise use and get some resources, but apply more tedious micromanagement and same ambush map repeated for me like 3 times. -Reapers are clearly more useful than other resistance soldiers in late game, especially if they roll good skills in training center,  i mean chain banish is just nonsense. -Faster map load times, to my understanding, load map in chunks, which leads to some walls to be non-existent, which will lead to hilarious stuff sometimes (not so hilarious on Ironman though), and you put 5 mods on and in lategame load times will be garbage anyway. -Lost zombieman dudes add atmosphere and more difficulty to some missions, but they turn advent even more stupid, and on fustercluck drops where you HAVE TO use a lot of grenades you can have like 40 lost on screen and your pc drops dead. -Resistance posters thing is straight up hilarious. Why in your struggle against xenos invaders you would use meme generator as propaganda machine is beyond me, but what do i know. -Alex Jones on resistance radio is top notch detail, but bloody bored burgers joke is... Well it seems to be itnended to be so bad it's good, but jesus f christ i hear something about those damn burgers every time i zoom out from tactical map. -New enemies are complete fannywellingtons, spectre is just straight up annoying and will die next turn anyway, because after his clone thing spectre just moves to ridiculous place and bends over for you to flank, havent seen his shadow do ANYTHING thorough entire game (started on commander and switched to legendary after like 8 hours). One thing i legit loved is new retaliation mission where you have militia fighting alongside you (even though it was done with a mod before). I advice you take mindshields with you though, because those cheeky militia buggers don't discriminate at which enemies to shoot, aliens or your mind controlled top waifu soldier. And one thing i hated is that CG videos can still lag and freeze and do other bullocks, it's very annoying when final cutscene just lags and you have your bloody sound dragging 10 seconds behind the video. Overall bugs with AI freeze and other really annoying garbage wasn't really adressed to my estimation. Overall all things considered it's nowhere near the level of quality of Enemy Within for first new XCOM in terms of expansion, it has lots of great stuff if you're to play it for the first or second time, but If you already played 20000 hours - i dunno, maybe with Long War it will be great, but i don't see such price to be justified until you're a real fan. Well i am and can't wait for TFTD remake sometime this century so i'm in.", "appid": "593380", "steamid": "profiles/76561198001384528", "voted_up": true, "votes_up": "2", "votes_funny": 0, "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1505822400.0}
