{"text": "An ungodly PoS. I initially wrote a lengthy review detailing all the game's many severe stability issues and severe optimization issues, making references to steady trends in negative reviews and lackluster elements in positive reviews, and highlighting the fact that the game won't even load into the main menu for me, nevermind into any actual gameplay, all because it's such a hot mess of a (and, going off other reviews, a semi-abandoned) game. But Steam ate that review, and this not-game isn't worth me rewriting a review to the same level of detail, just like it isn't worth giving any further consideration of trying to play it. And yeah, that hour of \"playtime\" I have? Not a Steam glitch (well, aside from it reporting a slightly lower playtime here than it does in my library, for some reason). That was all me trying to load in and getting crashes, lockups, or endless [I waited as long as 20 minutes, once, to be sure] loading screens. And yet, somehow, the game is using twice the memory and CPU that actual games of the same style would use during gameplay, all within the game's loading process. There's something severely busted with this program, and other reviews (even among positive ones) encourage that feeling of dubiousness towards it. In a nutshell, you're likely best to just avoid this one.", "appid": "611500", "steamid": "profiles/76561198031261101", "voted_up": false, "votes_up": "2", "votes_funny": 0, "early_access": true, "tstamp_created": 1596974400.0}
