{"text": "Initially I bought the gold upgrade because I wanted the fancy cosmetics Now, I use the gold upgrade to exploit the extra 4 characters you get by buying it.  1 - Nelson publicly said while in a talk that he uses the gold money to buy steam games, instead of supporting himself or using it to make the game development better, faster, etc. 2 - The DLC provides you with 4 extra characters that have completely different inventories, skills, etc. This is essentially P2W, as it lets anyone /w gold to store their loot on these characters (at which, such loot is unraidable and unaccessable by other players) Do I reccommend this 'DLC'? If you like the stuff it gives you, yes. But if you're here to buy the DLC to \"support the games development\" or anything like that, or if you're completely anti-P2W, I'd reccommend you DON'T buy the DLC. EDIT: I'm getting tons of comments from people that either don't know what they're talking about or have nothing meaningful to say. Small warning for you, if you post nonsense here it'll just get deleted.", "appid": "306460", "steamid": "profiles/76561198149274098", "voted_up": false, "votes_up": "6", "votes_funny": 0, "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1512043200.0}
