{"text": "This game is a joke, it's â™¥â™¥â™¥â™¥â™¥â™¥ and I've done everything I could to try to like it, heres why it stinks : -The whole building aspect of the game is not necessary at all, you can complete the main scenario without building anything... so it's just a pointless buggy waste of time to build anything. -The game has so many bugs, glitches... It's painful to even look at it, every cave looks the same -Fights are â™¥â™¥â™¥â™¥â™¥â™¥, hitboxes are always WAY wider than the enemies are actually -Weapons are all slow and half of them are pointless -When you use anything to produce some light its either : not enough or you have to push your damn L button a long ass time every two minutes to re-start your fire, worst UX ever -Is there really any UX job by the way ? (( UX = user experience, how handy are the game mechanics)) Because the building is a pain in the ass and takes so much time, for absolutely nothing in realilty. -IA is a joke, dumbest IA ever, enemies can be stuck in walls etc -Game looks like â™¥â™¥â™¥â™¥, 2008 called and they want they textures back, lmao. And the level designs are poor, who the â™¥â™¥â™¥â™¥ is in charge of these ? Those caves were awfully put together -The scenario is also â™¥â™¥â™¥â™¥â™¥â™¥â™¥â™¥, there is like alien weird technology whatsoever on the island, and you crashed, you look for your son, that has been taking down in the deepest caves, to a lab, stuck in an artefact â™¥â™¥â™¥â™¥-engine, and you have to extract him put an other girl/boy instead or destruct the complex and live for ever on that â™¥â™¥â™¥â™¥-island, I mean ... NO SENSE. There was no fresh corpse of scientist or whatever like that, it doesnt make any sense at all, who took the kid away ? There are just dumb cannibals we never know anything about, it's just a plain joke lmao [Next point is a personnal take on one aspect of the scenario] -Once a-â™¥â™¥â™¥â™¥â™¥â™¥â™¥-gain a video game that force us to be a parent/have a â™¥â™¥â™¥â™¥â™¥â™¥â™¥ children, why if we don't â™¥â™¥â™¥â™¥â™¥â™¥â™¥ want that ? This point is personal, I don't wanna be involved as a parent in a game AT ANYTIME, when will the â™¥â™¥â™¥â™¥â™¥â™¥â™¥ writters will learn that it's not appealing ? Not everyone want that.  TLDR : It's a â™¥â™¥â™¥â™¥â™¥â™¥â™¥ joke, it's â™¥â™¥â™¥â™¥â™¥â™¥, buggy, badly put together, doesnt hold any promises and building is useless, scenario written down by a 10 years old kid, DON'T BUY THIS CRAP.", "appid": "242760", "steamid": "profiles/76561198035844816", "voted_up": false, "votes_up": "1", "votes_funny": "2", "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1591704000.0}
{"text": "Promising but lacking in substance. Disregarding the technical issues, the game that promises to be a Ratchet & Clank clone is a discount version of a discount version of one. The entirety of the game can be completed in little over 2 hours and with a cast of bland characters saddled with cringe worthy dialogue, it was not worth the trouble of playing. Don't bother unless it is at steep discount and you are tired of playing solitaire/minesweeper for the Nth time.", "appid": "452540", "steamid": "profiles/76561197992906798", "voted_up": false, "votes_up": "8", "votes_funny": 0, "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1534507200.0}
