{"text": "Okay I'm rewriting this review after 30h playing now to point out the new stuff that makes me still believing the game is overpriced (but hey we're buying it still, it's Naheulbeuk... Mostly Frenchies there will buy it anyway)... And the review needed a rewrite because I'm being less spammed by the characters's lines when I switch between them in menus, must have been a bug corrected. Krayn did a live during the beta where he already pointed out that it'd be nice for us to not having to switch to the rogue to disarm traps, like we don't have to switch to the mage to put back tomes collections... I mean... Yeah, it's a bit annoying. Okay, you see the traps because it's just the same statue all over again, but it's still annoying to have to switch characters... And to be honest, in Epic, traps deal 18 damages at lvl 8, no care, just hit the trap. Potions are overpowered and make all other healing items (with statuses healing) just a joke. I'm playing Epic mode, I've sold everything that aren't bandages and potions, I'll tell you. I just heal the dots and use the healing on all characters. All hard fights have been done better with full potions in belt instead of trying to use saucages and other items... Agility is overpowered and makes build making dumb. Don't look over other stats, really guys, with 50+ parry and evasion, they just miss you all the time (combined with dwarf's and paladine's abilities, critical parries all the time lol). Also, full agility means you never miss, stat is too good. I don't mind it tho, now that I'm capped with it I'm going for a bit of strength/int ahah. The game is fine, won't be the most unforgetable experience but don't buy it full price if you can't, wait for Steam's sales... The stats stuff and potions stuff, the emptiness feeling you got while running with the highlight button makes me say that it's not worth the full price.", "appid": "970830", "steamid": "profiles/76561198022078581", "voted_up": false, "votes_up": "13", "votes_funny": "6", "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1600344000.0}
{"text": "Not a bad game at all if you like Chess. Problem is, the game is severely lacking in content (maps and chess piece models). It barely comes with anything and the DLCS are overpriced, most of which suck from the looks of it. If more effort went into options, maps, and chess pieces for the game instead of DLC, it could have been much better and more varied. Even if the price was increased for the base game it would have been worth it. Also the DLC is overpriced at full price even if you do like a few of them. As for the A.I., not sure how good it is but I don't think it is terrible. However, I am sure there are other chess games with better A.I.", "appid": "518060", "steamid": "profiles/76561198061656944", "voted_up": false, "votes_up": "13", "votes_funny": 0, "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1591531200.0}
