{"text": "Believe me when I say I really didn't want to give this game a thumbs down. I'm at the last chapter now and I have to say the narrative of this game did not disappoint, the story is fairly intriguing and most of the characters are believable and authentic. It's quite a nice looking game too, and the fact that it was made by an indie studio makes it all the more impressive. So why the thumbs down? Well, what this game achieved in storytelling and character building were, unfortunately, completely decimated by the gameplay. I knew this was a story-focused game made by an indie studio, so I expected the gameplay to be somewhat clumsy and tedious, but I thought it'd be fine as long as the story and the characters could make up for it. I'm sorry to say they didn't, at least not for me. The stealth, combat and puzzle solving, albeit largely monotonous, were all tolerable to me. Some parts of the game, however, were incredibly frustrating to go through--there were way too many times when I or my companion got instantly killed due to the game design being scuffed and confusing, and for that, I simply can't get myself to give this game a thumbs up. It's a shame, I really enjoyed the first half of this game, but I guess good things never last.", "appid": "752590", "steamid": "profiles/76561198177002086", "voted_up": false, "votes_up": "3", "votes_funny": 0, "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1581163200.0}
