{"text": "Unfortunately I have to agree with most of the recent reviews here. This game wasn't totally terrible, but new bunch of generic characters, which I couldn't make any kind of emotional bond with, made the game very boring for me. The plot was very repetitive, which I kinda understand since for me the whole \"zombie\" genre seems way too overused, so it's basically impossible to create anything new and groundbreaking with that theme.  I really wanted to see more of Clementine, now that she has grown a lot, but she had only few smaller scenes, which also made all the choices I had made in the previous games completely meaningless. I've been huge fan of the series (and Telltale games overall) and it feels really bad to give this a thumbs down, but I think they could've done so much better work with this. . . .", "appid": "536220", "steamid": "profiles/76561198081574980", "voted_up": false, "votes_up": "231", "votes_funny": "2", "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1496318400.0}
