{"text": "Hmmm.... where to start with this one.. This is one of those games where I wish Steam had an actual rating system instead of a thumbs up/thumbs down system because it would certainly be somewhere in between. As others have said, and as you may have noticed, there are a lot of similarities between this and Huniepop.  In fact, this basically borrows its entire concept from Huniepop.  Where this and Huniepop differ is that this doesn't appear to be quite as polished a product, and it certainly is a lot more difficult to progress in this game. I like match 3 games, but this one differs a bit from a regular match 3 game in that you can only move pieces left or right on the game board.  The game board then advances slowly towards the top of the play area revealing new rows of pieces on the bottom.  Once the board reaches the top, you have about 3 to 5 seconds to clear the top pieces before the game ends. The whole big deal though is that this game relies so much less on skill and 9 times out of 10 you are relying on the gods of RNG to grant you enough pieces to work with to make the matches required in order to keep the game going.  When you do find yourself out of luck and are forced to shuffle pieces from the top, it's not as simple as grabbing a piece and hastily moving it with your mouse.  The pieces move quite sluggishly which further complicates things.  I consider myself quite skilled at match 3 games... I actually did finish Huniepop.  But during a recent play session on this game, out of 4 rounds, I managed to win only 1 of them... I seem to remember a similar record during other play sessions.  At this rate, if this works at all like Huniepop, I'm headed very quickly towards the \"You are still single\" bad ending. However, not everything is totally terrible with this game.  The girls are drawn quite well and retain that \"I would like to see more\" aspect to them, if you get my meaning.  In similar style to a lot of other dating sims, the music gives you that crazy \"I'm stuck in an elevator\" feel to it.  What little of the voice acting I heard was OK, but I preferred it off because some of it was actually sorta cheesy.  But that's one other bonus to the game... it allows playing with the voices off! But, to sum things up, even though there is some playability here, I'm going to have to give this a thumbs down for now.  Maybe if the gameplay was reworked a bit to make it a bit less difficult to actually win due to skill rather than pure luck, it would be easier to grant this a passing grade. I suppose it comes down to this:  Are you willing to pay money for a game that is like Huniepop only to have the content you want to see (the reason you wanted to buy this game, right?  *wink wink* *nudge nudge*) walled off behind some unnecessarily difficult puzzles?", "appid": "576590", "steamid": "profiles/76561197995204251", "voted_up": false, "votes_up": "5", "votes_funny": 0, "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1487505600.0}
