{"text": "After playing through the whole thing I can safely say: ALL HOPE IS LOST. All you do is walk through random areas riddled with assets and badly written English instructions. I mean if you have a whole bunch of assets you have to get a good use out of them, right? Occasionally you'll come across some enemies floating or just standing around - nothing will actively try to kill you. The only thing that can kill you is time itself - that is if your survival meters drop to zero.  What? You thought a time traveling Viking doesnt have to drink and eat? Better keep that \"Thirst\" and \"Hungry\" meter filled up or you'll slowly starve to death. The other things facing their untimely end will be your frames per second and your sanity and patience. The closest you'll ever get to actual gameplay is in the driving section but thats not saying a lot since the controls are delayed as all hell and awful. As an extra bonus to make it more annoying, you can get stuck on almost everything. So in the end this is one boring asinine asset fest and you'll wish you'd have done something useful with your time, like knitting or flower arrangement. Now if you'll excuse me, I have to figure out how to build a time machine so I can stop myself from ever playing this one.", "appid": "522570", "steamid": "profiles/76561198035386752", "voted_up": false, "votes_up": "69", "votes_funny": "35", "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1493985600.0}
