{"text": "The game   perfect before the last update. Now they force us to pay if we want what we could get before for free (or you can play twice the time you played before for that). I mean, you get Monkey Money (MM) in-game, you use that to buy new heroes, consumables and heroes skins. So you could use that MM early to get new heroes and have fun with the hero of your choice. Since the last update you have to pay MM to assign points in Knowledge Trees (high amount of MM, enough to buy all heroes and skins). If you don't know, Knowledge Trees are very important, they give your monkeys some benefits (like reducing their cost, increasing their power, range, allowing you to place more limited monkeys). So... if you want to assign points in your Knowledge Trees like old players, you'll have to spend your Monkey Money (something they didn't have to do)... now you have to choose between buying new heroes or knowledge trees early game. You can pay some dollars to get MM, or you spend many hours to farm a small amout. If you are a casual gamer, if you can't (or don't want to) spend all day playing to get MM and have more fun with the benefits of knowledge trees or new heroes... this game is not for you. I used to play Bloons TD 6 only with my brother or friends sometimes, some co-op fun (not all day), now it sucks, we had to farm before, but now... 2x more. It affects new and low level players, that is why high level people (or people who plays all day) aren't bothered with that change. Thank you, Ninja Kiwi for this stupid update and your predatory practices (like they do with Bloons TD Adventure Time).", "appid": "960090", "steamid": "profiles/76561198117728135", "voted_up": false, "votes_up": "30", "votes_funny": "1", "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1580040000.0}
