{"text": "Bought the Deluxe Version because I am a fool. Guess what, they thought that after receiving my 55â‚¬ that I was unworthy to listen to their soundtrack, so I need to pay an extra 7â‚¬ if I want to do so. Hahahaha! Either way, been playing this game non-stop, and while the game is somewhat decent, it feels like EU: rome 1.5. The character system is still weak, although with slight improvements. The economy is still pratically non-existent as well (like in EU:rome), you need to conquer more pratically if you want to earn more money, but there are a couple of limited alternatives unlike in EU: Rome. Militarily, the game is pretty identical, but with some slight changes as well - you can change battle tactic for instance. The map did get a lot more provinces than EU: Rome, so in many casses (many wars with big nations included) the computer lags and I got a very modern computer with a very good processor (+SSD) so the problem isn't my own. All in all, the game is decent, but I am downvoting due to the \"Empty\" feeling you get after playing 1.0. Knowing Paradox's latest policies, they will charge you more than 200â‚¬ for DLCs to give the game the complexity it needs. Hell, in this one, you even got to pay for the soundtrack at launch (even on Deluxe edition), ridiculous. EDITED: Many people seem to like to point out that CK2 and EU4 were not polished products  when they were released, but they were a vast improvement over their previous game (CK1 and EU3 respectively). Imperator is almost the same as EU: Rome, so the \"improvement\"  is pretty small, definetely smaller when compared to CK2-CK1 and EU4-EU3.", "appid": "859580", "steamid": "profiles/76561198002025072", "voted_up": false, "votes_up": "93", "votes_funny": "2", "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1556366400.0}
