{"text": "TLDR: Cannot recommend this game even at 50% off. For $12 you get 2 hour of content and the only unique aspect of the game wears off quickly.  The novelty of timestop wears off quickly after the first chapter. The sound cue in the game is terrible. Groups of enemies that spawned and shoot behind you doesn't give any sound until you die from them. Even segments of level where you're supposed to dodge moving vehicles doesn't make any sound.  Story wise, the way the story of told is also counter intuitive. The protagonist is essentially chatting with another person in a messaging app. You can't just sit back and enjoy the story because you have to spam random keys on your keyboard and hit ENTER for the story to progress. With such a boring plot and no interesting characters the games' attempt to break the 4th wall feels forced and cringy. Content wise, if you're decent at fps games you should be able to finish the campaign in 2 hours. You'll unlock an endless mode and challenges but lets be real, if the campaign is boring and short, I doubt the other modes offer much. I hate the main menu. No mouse function, doesn't give much info on the settings or anything at all and a lot of garbage unnecessary content.", "appid": "322500", "steamid": "profiles/76561197993221115", "voted_up": false, "votes_up": "11", "votes_funny": "3", "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1549195200.0}
