{"text": "Hello there; Without a doubt Blood is one of the BEST FPS ever. But we all know that.  What I am reviewing here today, is not Blood itself. It is Blood FS (Fresh Supply). It is its first day on the market, so these issues may change. I will change my review as the game updates. The source code for Blood was never released. All that exists is a leaked 0.96 alpha source code, which has been used to reverse engineer these fan ports. FS is not a sourceport. No port for Blood is a sourceport, sadly. FS uses the Kex engine to emulate Blood. GDX ported the Build engine to Java and runs off the leaked alpha source code. Nblood uses the Build engine and reversed engineered 1.21 debug code. These are the difference between the ports at a base level.  What I will be reviewing is FS's capabilities, its pro and cons, and how it compares to Fan ports like Nblood and GDX. I have played Blood to my heartâ€™s desire for the past two years now in DOSbox, Nblood, and GDX. I beat it for the first time on normal (Lightly broiled) is DOSBox, then Well-done on GDX. Nblood I have played often; and used it to beat a heavily surreal and fascinating fan mappack called Deathwish. I have even made a map for Blood. I know Blood very well; so playing this port, surprisingly feels new. I will illustrate the difference between FS and the other ports briefly.  First off, yes it works fine and runs at high FPS if you wish it too. It is obviously superior to DOSbox, but that's like comparing an ant to an elephant. I will be comparing FS to fanports keep in mind, and not DOSBox. Why? Because why would anyone pay ten bucks for an inferior version of a game, you could get better elsewhere? Differences which are both good and bad: The new renderer looks amazing and is very colorful. However, it is a huge stray-away from the original Blood colors. If you want some new looks, this is good. If you prefer the OG colors, (Which I do), it will be a heavy problem. The Proâ€™s FS has: Revamped music. It works. It is good publicity for Blood, which for sure needs more attention. Improved AI, monsters instead of bumping into walls now chase after you and are more aggressive. (Easily the best improvement).  New Voxel sprites. Supports direct x and other 3d renderers. New Netcode for multiplayer Some cons; here are the major issues first: Changing settings in display options creates a black screen and forces an FS restart. No software renderer, it contains only palate emulation. (hence the polar opinion on the colors). FS comes with Bloodâ€™s files, but not all of them. So, if you wanna do some modding or mapediting; itâ€™ll very difficult. You may have to go to some websites and download those programs yourself. It does not come with all the original Blood files.  Limited modding capabilities Nitpick Cons and glitches: Booting up Cryptic Passage requires exiting and re-entering (which in GDX CP is natively supported). Not being able to make the hud bigger or lesser with - and +  Everything looks wonky using mouse aim, even without 3D aim on, everything is more warped than usual for a Build engine game. The end screen for levels having the same resolution as DosBox instead of being wide-screen. Changing between CD music and MIDI requires restarting the level Thatâ€™s all so far. Blood is an amazing game for sure. FS is close to doing it some justice. I have other issues but they are more personal and most players wonâ€™t care for. For example, the console takes up 2/3â€™s of the screen! That nitpick is far too nitpicky to be an issue! FS has a lot of these small nitpicks, but the ones listed do add up. FS as it stands on day one release, is on-par with Nblood and GDX. It is not superior to these FAN ports, nor is it less. Is it worth ten bucks? Iâ€™d say no; for now. Once the nitpick cons are fixed, the glitches in settings patched, and you have the option of owning all of Bloodâ€™s OG files, then yes, for sure, ten bucks is well worth it. I have faith that Nightdive will fix these issues. Wait another few weeks, and if they are fixed, buy it. As for now, best to stick with fanports. I will give FS a thumb up when it becomes better than the fan ports and is fixed. I must review it based on the current product. I really do hope that it becomes a Thumbs up in my book very soon....", "appid": "1010750", "steamid": "profiles/76561198262740982", "voted_up": false, "votes_up": "186", "votes_funny": "21", "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1557403200.0}
