{"text": "Okay so I bought this game for one reason, having fun with friends, but unfortunately I got very rarely in that situation, so i played solo's. I'm giving this game a negative rating, not because it's not fun, or the game is just bad, no, and because of the performance and optimization of the game, I got to say, the optimization is really bad when it comes to crashes, and drop frames, because I played only 3 hours(so that means that I'm not willing to refund, I respect my decision once it's done), and this 3 hours, the experience was terrible, but fun at some points, terrible because of the crashes, to be more exact, approximately 5-6 crashes in 3 hours, which is very bad for the price of the game, but as I said it was also fun, first of all because I like battle-royale games, but also that the mechanics of the game are pretty cool, like the inventory management and shooting. With all of this I give it a negative rating, because this game from what I saw and heard was one of the best battle-royales out there. I will give it a final conclusion after I play a bit more and maybe after they make more updates fixing all the bugs and crashes and some features in the game... OK, Here we go, I now have 13 hours in the game, and no, I am not changing my rating because this game is literally impossible for beginners, and I say that not because I wasn't good at the game, because I am good at more than 10 wins, the thing is I see this game to be really hard, there are so many campers, and on top 10 people remaining, that's very not good, and also about the optimization of the game, I think they made a update, because the crashes are not that often now, and fps is slightly better, BUT, the DROP FRAMES in this game are incredible, like i can't believe it, literally every time I land it drops 100 frames, and I teleport 10 meters away from the spot I initially landed. Moreover I said to myself that maybe 13 hours is not enough to find the fun in this game, and no, that's not true at all, I say that because in this 13 hours I played maybe 100-200 matches in which the most of them, I died instantly without even picking a weapon, the only way to get in the top 10 is to go to a really far away place from the plane itself, but most of the time you end up dying in the zone, which also it's a bad thing about this game, literally the vehicles are very rare, and without a vehicle you can't reach the zone, only if you start running very early, because the zone it's just too fast.And one more thing, I don't recommend buying this game at this period of time, because there are just too many pro's(campers), that will not let you win ever, and that's even worse if you are a person that is not that good at shooting, or learning the mechanics of the game very slow, trust me, this game was worth it, it had it's own time, but now, it's just broken. Here I am once again, saying something about this game after another 84 hours of game play.After all of this time, I observed something, first of all, i resolved the drop frames, and the textures not loading, by moving the game in the SSD, I am conscious that I have 8GB of ram, but, that shouldn't be a problem, because the minimum requirement for this game is 8GB, so it should run just fine, if they benchmarked the game accordingly. While playing this game for a while now, I observed that even if I resolved the game performance, the game gets very, very boring, because, first of all, sometimes queues are extra long and also the majority of the game, you will loot, maximum loot, and be ready to fight, but when it comes to the fight in like top 20-10, one guy will come from nowhere and kill you in an instant, that happens almost everytime if you're not camping houses, and you actually move for fighthing, and that's really annoying. I didn't talk about the hackers in this game, but, after playing this long, I observed why people we're saying that there are a lot of hackers in this game, the thing is the hackers in this game, are very sneaky about it, and in the death cam, you'll probably never gonna observe it, only if maybe he has a really strong aimbot, but with wall-hack, I can't see how you would ever observe it, they just hide it very good. They promised a new update in which they are gonna fix all the performance problems and the hackers, I'm gonna wait for that update, and i'll update this review, if something has really changed, I'm really looking forward to it.", "appid": "578080", "steamid": "profiles/76561198327508005", "voted_up": false, "votes_up": "1", "votes_funny": 0, "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1583064000.0}
