{"text": "Here are some pros and cons for this game. Pros- -The sniper classes work well, and the pistols are nice. -Has a few decent maps. -The game itself looks decent.  -Runs smoothly. -Cool community Cons- -Anything that isn't a sniper rifle or pistol has an unrealistic amount of kick for a trained soldier.  -Some maps have an insane amount of fog making it impossible to see people even with a sniper rifle. -Any night map is unplayable, because of how dark it is, and people blend into the background. Some other maps have a really bad layout and on one map the one side has a high point advantage making it hard for one team to push or even fight back. -Night Vision Goggles? Yeah no, just insane brightness that kills your eyes.  -Failed realism. Aimed for realism with a 1 hit kill with pretty much any gun, but as already stated they didn't put realistic recoil, weapon spread, loadouts(about to talk about this more) -The class loadouts are strangely done. When picking certain attachments, and what not for classes you have a limited amount of points for items in your layout. Are you on a terrible night map, and want to try the broken NVG? Now you have to choose what you want to keep at attachments for your guns, and use some of those points for Night Vision Goggles. You are probably thinking that seems balance, but it isn't. Do you want a scope, silencer, and the NVG? Sucks for you, because you can only have two of those things at a time which limits you.  -1 - 2 hit kill system. As I stated they aimed for realism when it comes to killing people, but that is where they stopped. Since they didn't actually make anything else realistic, they should have not made the kill system realistic.  -Respawning in waves. The only game my friend, and I could get in within 2 hours was Push. The system is insanely flawed. If one team pushes another team back they can easily spawn kill. They can just camp the spawn (it being all in one little area) and mow the one team down until they run out or reinforcements. -Horrible hit registration. I had my shots \"miss\" multiple times when I was aimed on a guy standing still when I was using a sniper rifle. The bullet would go through them, and this happened to my friend playing with me while he was using the m4a1. - No competitive as of 2016-07-01. (July, 1st, 2016). Although competitive mode for this game is in production it is not yet, and the game has been out for over 2 years. Conclusions:  With the many problems I faced while playing this game, and lack of a competitive mode I cannot recommend this game to anybody.  Although I can see that the developers worked hard on this game, I do not believe it is a purchase that is worth the price. At $16.99 CDN full price, or $5.09 sale price I do not believe either of those prices are worth it.", "appid": "222880", "steamid": "profiles/76561198157490578", "voted_up": false, "votes_up": 0, "votes_funny": 0, "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1467288000.0}
