{"text": "Yes the game is cute and can be fun for a few hrs but it gets old fast. The game is def early access material at best. I would not recommend buying the game in its current statues or price. Now this is a quick and simple review based on only 11hrs of gameplay. The things I already find boring and annoying about the game is how slow progression is. You feel like all you are doing is quest after quest and you are punished for adventuring.  You can either open your shop and spam E for mins and make some money but waste the entire day doing just that. Explore but you wont be able to run your shop (reason i suggest 2 players but 1 is stuck bored af with this chore) Even exploring needs work because those chest you get give you flowers most of the time which to begin with getting those chest takes time and effort only to get a freaking flower. A flower sells for only 10 why not just give the player the gold instead of having to not only go get the chest now they must run the shop to sell it?? You also have these other neat stations you can setup. Yeah sure I can raise chickens, cats and even have my own \"farm\" where I can so farm plant flowers and this gets boring quick for me. I would like to see them level up for some extra rewards. I just expect more depth out of this game but it is simple enough for anyone to play for max a few hrs and drop. Anyone looking for a casual game this might be a fit but dont set yourself for much of an expectation until further updates if fixes do happen. I lost a chicken that disapeared after the save.  Cute: yes Depth: none storyline: none  Casual game only will update the game review once bigger updates come", "appid": "840010", "steamid": "profiles/76561198079748456", "voted_up": false, "votes_up": "65", "votes_funny": "4", "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1545825600.0}
