{"text": "I am sorry guys, but I can't recommend this game. If you want a better way to start with Samurai Jack, watch all 5 seasons, that series is perfection. SPOILERS Okay, I of course was not expecting a masterpiece, as I am sure no one else was either, but for 40 dollars, I at least expected something decent. The story starts off where season 5 finale left off, you are about to head back in time to your homeland, but along the way, Aku manages to catch Jack and send him back to where he began his entire adventure, now you are going through all sorts of time portals, experiencing the shows most iconic places, meeting the most beloved characters of the show..(The Scotsman, Sam-Moo-Rhai, etc), and battling other well know villains and robots.  Jack has to find these Aku medallions and destroy them to advance further in time and get back to his home world. Right off the bat when you start the game, it looks terrible, the graphics seriously look like they can give late PS2 a run for it's money, character animations are horrid, and the gameplay/controls in general are stiff and clunky.  Keep in mind this is a third person hack n' slash, and holy balls is it basic, this whole game felt like a PS2 game, everything was outdated looking.  As with all hack n' slash, you will go through the games 8-9 worlds, leveling up your character and weapons with basic attack, defense, combos, the works..you collect coins and sort of magical fire/aura on the way to charge up your attacks. Sam-Moo-Rhai owns a store where you can buy, sell, upgrade, and repair your weapons and get healing items and other magical trinkets to aid you in battle. At the end of each stage is the obvious boss battle...and they suck.. I have never been so bored with end level bosses, and these take the cake, their attacks are easily choreographed and avoidable. Same thing can't be said for the main enemies, there are some parts where they all gang up on you and it is so broken, I had to use my haggis or hot water all up because I was trapped in a corner and like 10 zombies or metal bugs took their turns in a congo line to take shots at me. Their hit detections are atrocious and they hit you from across the galaxy with ease. Only really good thing about this was over time when you take damage, you lose pieces of your clothing and appear battle worn as in the shows, which was a nice detailed touch. That is pretty much it, music is okay at times but most it just feels generic, the whole thing just feels like a PS2 remake and not in a good way. I can't recommend the game for it's price, 40 bucks is not worth 5 hours of repetitive gameplay and boring outdated visuals. Trust me, if you want a better experience, watch the show instead, much...MUCH better!", "appid": "1150590", "steamid": "profiles/76561198117831388", "voted_up": false, "votes_up": "17", "votes_funny": "2", "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1598356800.0}
