{"text": "If you don't own the Deluxe Edition, I won't recommend you to buy it at all. The Deluxe Edition features a bit extra content, including this Farewell Episode. Considered the price, it felt like I got absolutely nothing out of it. You're playing as Max, right before you're leaving Seattle. You're at Chloe's house, where all you do is digging up old things, finding old letters and running around doing pointless things. The outcome of what you put time in, was not satisfying or interesting at all. I'm a huge fan of the Life Is Strange games, and I recommend buying all the games in the franchise. But if you're not already owning the Deluxe Edition, I won't recommend buying it. Not for this. While Farewell Episode aren't supposed to mean a lot, I feel a lot more work could've been put into this episode.", "appid": "763780", "steamid": "profiles/76561198142169767", "voted_up": false, "votes_up": "4", "votes_funny": 0, "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1520424000.0}
