{"text": "It feels like recent Total war titles all suffer from CA trying too hard to put every possible idea and system into each game. Everything about this game is great, the design, the assets, the research and the overall effort is all immense. But there is simply TOO MUCH going on. The UI is confused and overflowing with TOO MUCH. The province management is excessive. The character management is excessive. There are too many stories being told in these games. After trying a few hours of this, I re-installed Shogun 2 to compare. While none of the Total war games is perfect (Diplomacy and naval battles in SG2 are poor), Shogun 2 hit a sweet spot in terms of scale and the game-play loop. I hope CA will keep refining their games and cut back some of the bells and whistles.", "appid": "779340", "steamid": "profiles/76561198009205423", "voted_up": false, "votes_up": "3", "votes_funny": "2", "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1603281600.0}
