{"text": "I can't even believe how broken this game is. I really hate saying that beacause this game had a lot going for it, great graphics, interesting plot, good sounds, it has so much potential to be a good game but it's just not. And let me tell you why. First 30 mins into the game and I was really enjoying it! The map was huge and was nice to look at, I was keeping a steedy pace on my progress, the story kept me involved and I wanted to keep playing to find out what was going on. Also the scares weren't amazing, just jumpscares but sometimes it could manage to send chills down your spine when you least expect it. After an hour or so I ran into my first enemy that I could fight, all I had was a crowbar and all I could do was go up to the monster and hit it, then move back a little to avoid it's attack and then go back up to hit it again, rinse and repeat until the monster dies. The combat system felt awkward and slow, but it didn't bother me much and I could forgive the game for bad cambat as the game doesn't really focuse on that. From there it just goes down hill. Each time you compleat an objective, Slenderman gets more aggressive as you would expect, BUT he starts teleporting you at random and you never know where you'll end up. It wouldn't be so bad if the map wasn't so FREAKING HUGE and it wasn't every time you were five feat from the freaking objective. So you spend a while running from one point of the map to the other a good three times until Slenderman decides you've had enough and leaves you alone for a few minutes.....then he's off to it again!!!! I guess the developer wanted you to feel relieved once you FINALLY make it to your destination and escaped the horrifying torment Slenderman was putting you through. Instead it completely ruins the atmosphere because it becomes SO predictable and boring and nothing ever happens, you're not even scared anymore you're just pissed at how much of your time Slender is wasting and you want to punch him in the face whenever he shows up  for being a douche. After awhile it feels like he's trolling you. I pushed through and kept playing thinking I could deal with it, but then it got supper buggy! Whenever I came across a page it wouldn't let me pick it up even though it made a sound like I did but it wasn't in my inventory, witch is very important if you want to know the story and continue with the game. I tried to ignore that and kept playing even though I wouldn't know anything of what was going on. Eventually I found a key that unlocked a gate that I needed to backtrack to. On my way to the gate though I noticed items laying around that I had already picked up. It was like I hadn't been in that area before even though those items were from the first objective in the game and it was like I was replaying the beginning. After going through a few things that I already did I died, just like that, for no reason!! I loaded up my last save and tried to do the same thing, but this time I didn't get very far becuase it's like the game totaly reset itself and I couldn't even go ANYWHERE!!! My last save was in this prison looking place and the gate that I had to unlock with a code was colsed and you could only unlock it from the outside!!!! So I was locked in this prison with Slender teleporting me around the prison yard with no way out!! I even closed the game and tried again and I WAS STILL STUCK! Two freaking hours of my life wasted on this horrifying game! Not because it was scary but because it was tedious to go through!!  I'm hoping the DLC can save this game. It's a shame because this game looks promising. But everything that makes a horror game good this game just didn't do right. If it did it didn't make up for the mistakes. The score I would give this game would be a 4/10. I did NOT have a good experience with this game and would recomend ANY horror game other than this! Save your time and memory and avoid this title.", "appid": "241640", "steamid": "profiles/76561198112469075", "voted_up": false, "votes_up": "3", "votes_funny": "1", "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1390564800.0}
