{"text": "This is a pretty solid, polished fps game with a huge amount of gamemodes, gun modification combinations and extra items for your loadouts. The game itself is very good but some things really let it down. - The bots play in a very robotic fashion. The only difficulty they ever create is the way they quick aim even when you're not in their field of view. This would be cheating from a real player and the bots move in a very dumb way so it's not a very good way to practice a lot.  - The ping and framerate are absolutely â™¥â™¥â™¥â™¥â™¥â™¥ in this. I have a top end laptop better than a lot of desktop PC's and I can run extremely demanding games such as Planetside2 with minimal lag but bo2 lacks efficiency and I experience random framerate drops even on the lowest settings. It is extremely rare to see my ping below 100 despite living in Australia, if you don't have servers here then that's pretty â™¥â™¥â™¥â™¥â™¥â™¥â™¥ stupid because you definately have the money for it and there are over 23 million people here. Sometimes I can't join a match that gives me less than 200ping. Rendering it unplayable - Bots don't allow many gamemdoes such as the party gamemodes. This is just plain laziness once again. This wouldn't take much extra programming and I've wanted to play gamemodes that have no proper matches I can join at the time in bots but can't, which brings me to my next point. - The players. This game is â™¥â™¥â™¥â™¥â™¥â™¥â™¥ dead. You could say that's because of it's age but it's not even that old. There are much older games and fps with a huge player base compared to this. You need to make an effort to have PC players too, otherwise the few that are still here will leave. Advertise and incentive, maybe more sales? But the thing that pisses me off the most is that half the games that do seem to run on here still I can't join. It will just say there is nothing to connect with.  I never played much cod but I enjoyed this game despite all the absolute bullsh*t from the above points. Unless someone could assure me though those problems would be fixed in a future cod I would never buy another game from the franchise or ever recommend to someone else. There is nothing stopping you from fixing this game, either. But that just wouldn't get you enough money, would it? Don't buy it.", "appid": "202970", "steamid": "profiles/76561198138291940", "voted_up": false, "votes_up": 0, "votes_funny": "1", "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1449921600.0}
