{"text": "This game sounds great on paper, the trailers and probably videos made about this game all seem FUN and wonderful, the graphics are really good, the models and the animations are as well! However... The game is just plain boring, all you have to do is: Walk to water Drink Walk to AI dino/Edible bush Eat Sit in a bush and wait for your dino to get slightly bigger Repeat until adult, then suicide when you want to grow something else. At the beginning, you are a little, slow, and weak dinosaur (Juvenile/Subadult stage) and you have to grow to adult, however there is literally nothing to do, and since you are slow and weak you are very vulnerable to other players attacks, and since you dont want to die then you need to hide and stay silent since as soon as something faster than you spots you, you are dead. The most effective way of playing this game is by not playing, you can get your food and water stats up and then sit in a bush in a forest, and feed your dino each 20 mins or so. Its a waste of money right now, and the devs are also pretty inactive, they have been busy with this \"recode\" that has been taking like, almost a year WITHOUT any updates or sneak peeks. The devs arent even giving us updates on how this \"recode\" is going and if you try to question it you'll just be met with hostility by both the devs and the fanboys who will tell you how HARD the devs are working 24hrs a day to recode the game. It is a glorified chatbox, and you'll end up leaving the game running while you watch netflix or youtube, so just watch netflix or youtube instead of throwing money away", "appid": "376210", "steamid": "profiles/76561198124048645", "voted_up": false, "votes_up": 0, "votes_funny": 0, "early_access": true, "tstamp_created": 1574424000.0}
