{"text": "As much as I love Sea of Thieves I cannot and I will never give it a positive review. One of the main reasons for giving it a negative review, is the fact that the game is being advertise as being \"SINGLE-PLAYER\" but you always need to be connected to the internet to play the game, you will always connect to a server to play the game and you will always encounter players. Yes, I am aware that is a pirate game and encountering players is the purpose of the game. You will go and find loot and travel around different island and inevitable others will come and loot you. If you want to play this game alone, will be incredibly hard, almost close to impossible and you will never enjoy the game by playing it alone. Sometimes I wish that I will just join a private server and just roam around the map to do whatever I want without the fear of encountering other players, perhaps with reduces xp + gold. It's incredibly frustrating to work for your loot for 3-4 hours as a \"SINGLE-PLAYER\" and then a Galleon, which is a boat of 4 players will come and attack you, and lose all the loot. You cannot win 4 v 1 and you will lose all your will to play the game. Do I like the game? Yes I do, I almost love the game, but the fact that you are always required to play with some else is unacceptable.", "appid": "1172620", "steamid": "profiles/76561198102283077", "voted_up": false, "votes_up": "4", "votes_funny": 0, "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1603454400.0}
