{"text": "I'm a big fan of the VtM setting and of visual novels (and of paradox, for that matter), so I had  pretty high expectations from this title. Alas, I really cannot recommend this game.  It's not a bad game, mind you. Art direction is good, writing is decent, although plot is nothing to write home about. Some of the characters are quite interesting (D'Angelo the nosferatu I really liked). What is wrong with this game is the \"game\" part. I've read a lot of \"choose youe  own adventure\" books in my childhood, so I think I can see a good one when I see it. Coteries of New York is just not one of them.  When you have a chioice to make, it always feels like a coin flip, as you do not have any element to base your choice on. That basically ruins the entire experience for me. I would have enjoyed it more as a simple visual novel, without choices to make. Just tell me a good story and we're ok. I just hope we'll have  better luck with Bloodlines 2.", "appid": "1096410", "steamid": "profiles/76561198054513832", "voted_up": false, "votes_up": "21", "votes_funny": "1", "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1587211200.0}
