{"text": "I decided to buy this Newgrounds flash port and give it a try when it was showcased at PAX Prime and when it got the recommendation of Markiplier. After slightly above 10 minutes of gameplay, it became pretty obvious that this game is a complete piece of trash and I've got no interest in subjecting myself to anymore of this half-baked and unpolished game. Here are some pros and cons... Pros: â€¢There is a tinge of humour which actually made me chuckle once or twice. â€¢The cartoonish art style is pretty good. â€¢Weapons seem powerful with the FX that the game inplements. â€¢The soundtrack is decent. Cons: â€¢The game lacks polishing with bugs and crashes popping up ever so often. â€¢Extremely low FPS despite my build having more than enough VRAM and processing power which is stated in the -requirements. â€¢Freezes ever so often and \"graphic intensive\" parts, especially boss fights. â€¢The only penalty for dying is a 2 second respawn delay which in some cases will respawn you in a solid object, forcing you to restart the level. â€¢Horrible hitbox detection on enemies, destroyable blocks and such. â€¢A +/- resolution changer which DOES NOT have any effect on the horrible FPS... Wait seriously? â€¢Some achievement do not have the correct requirements stated on them. â€¢All the levels are trial and error. â€¢Most if not all of the artwork is reused, creating a very repeated atmosphere which is not at all enjoyable. â€¢Controls are mediocre at best. The \"laser jetpack\" at the first few levels completely killed it for me. â€¢Completely out of place images above the height limit etc.  â€¢The pointer is not locked in the game, so windowed mode players beware.  All in all, I do not recommend this game if it's price stays anything above 1 USD.  It's a F2P game that somehow managed to get a $4 pricetag slapped on it. Do not buy unless you like fighting with the lag/controls instead of playing with the actual game.", "appid": "227280", "steamid": "profiles/7656119