{"text": "This game was so dissappointing that I am actually angry. Do not get fooled by the nice artstyle and the interesting topic. The screesnshots on the store page already show everything there is to this game. The gameplay loop consists of reading e-mails with information everyone who has even slightly researched this topic already knows, followed by the \"interactive\" sequences of preparing a body, during which the game tells you where exactly to click step-by-step every single time you do it. Afterwards you get to click an arrow on the ground to go to the other room, where you can click on the coffin or urn and click on the relatives to make a speech bubble with a pointless remark (\"She would have loved this funeral!\") appear, click another arrow to go back to your e-mails. Rinse and repeat for about 45 -60 minutes, depending on how you fast you can work through the mails. This should be free. Avoid at all cost.", "appid": "578720", "steamid": "profiles/76561198128285066", "voted_up": false, "votes_up": "6", "votes_funny": "1", "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1604404800.0}
