{"text": "It's a fidget spinner game. You, uh, spin the thing. You get an achievement for opening it. Whoop-dee-doo. I don't have high expectations when it comes to this kind of game, and generally really enjoy giddy silliness, but my overall disappointment with this game can be summed up in one word: Swastika.  For real. That's one of the spinners. Not cool, nazi. Now I have to go play Wolfenstein for an hour just to even out the bad karma.", "appid": "657630", "steamid": "profiles/76561197975413392", "voted_up": false, "votes_up": 0, "votes_funny": "1", "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1592740800.0}
{"text": "Even though the gameplay is clunky as hell, I still managed to enjoy it. A lot of text is still in chinese or translated badly, I still enjoyed it. Dragons are absolutely the opposite of fun, but it was still fine. Limited amount of dungeons per day? Sure thing. Overpowered whales killing you during events were just too much, along with a wide variety of paywalls that stop your progress all the time. Even when you get a special chest, you gotta top up the cash to actually get a key to open it or you did not get the chest at all. Oh well, too bad.", "appid": "1104290", "steamid": "profiles/76561197979538976", "voted_up": false, "votes_up": "13", "votes_funny": 0, "early_access": true, "tstamp_created": 1597665600.0}
